{
    "openapi": "3.0.0",
    "info": {
        "title": "User Management API endpoints (v3.4)",
        "description": "Admin user read endpoints that expose account lockout state via the `lock_until` field.\n\n## lock_until Field\n\nThe `lock_until` field indicates whether a user account is currently locked due to failed login attempts (see Account Lockout configuration).\n\n| Value | Meaning |\n|-------|--------|\n| `null` | Account is **not locked** |\n| ISO 8601 datetime (future) | Account is locked until this timestamp. Used by `auto_only` and `manual_or_auto` policies. |\n| `9999-12-31T00:00:00Z` | Account is locked **indefinitely** until a System Admin manually unlocks it (`manual_only` policy). |\n\nAn account is considered locked when `lock_until` is not `null` and `lock_until > now()`.\n\n## v3.4 Changes from v3\n\nThese endpoints are identical to their v3 counterparts except that every `UserResponse` item includes `lock_until`. Use these endpoints when the UI or integration needs to display lockout status.\n\n## Required Permissions\n\n- **List / Search / Read user**: Requires `user:read` permission\n- **Search with `all=true`**: Requires System Admin role\n- **Search without `group_id`**: Requires `user:readall` permission, or Group Admin with `allow_group_admin_access_unassigned` starter-pack config enabled",
        "version": "1.0.0"
    },
    "paths": {
        "/api/v3.4/users/": {
            "get": {
                "tags": [
                    "User Management"
                ],
                "summary": "List Users",
                "description": "Retrieve a paginated list of users accessible to the caller.\n\nEach user item includes the `lock_until` field for lockout visibility.\n\n### Pagination\n\n- `skip`: Number of records to skip (default: 0)\n- `limit`: Maximum number of records to return (default: 10)\n\n### Sorting\n\nPrefix a field with `-` for descending order (e.g. `-created_at`).",
                "operationId": "list_users_api_v3_4_users__get",
                "security": [
                    {
                        "MyHTTPBearer": []
                    }
                ],
                "parameters": [
                    {
                        "name": "sort",
                        "in": "query",
                        "required": false,
                        "schema": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "enum": [
                                "id",
                                "username",
                                "first_name",
                                "last_name",
                                "display_name",
                                "last_login",
                                "created_at",
                                "updated_at",
                                "-id",
                                "-username",
                                "-first_name",
                                "-last_name",
                                "-display_name",
                                "-last_login",
                                "-created_at",
                                "-updated_at"
                            ],
                            "default": "id"
                        },
                        "description": "Field to sort results by. Prefix with `-` for descending order."
                    },
                    {
                        "name": "skip",
                        "in": "query",
                        "required": false,
                        "schema": {
                            "type": "integer",
                            "minimum": 0,
                            "default": 0
                        },
                        "description": "Number of records to skip for pagination"
                    },
                    {
                        "name": "limit",
                        "in": "query",
                        "required": false,
                        "schema": {
                            "type": "integer",
                            "minimum": 0,
                            "default": 10
                        },
                        "description": "Maximum number of records to return"
                    }
                ],
